# Loomis — API Conventions

## Route Registration
All routes are registered under `/api/v1/`. Use Fastify's plugin system — one file per resource.
```typescript
// src/modules/finance/routes/payments.routes.ts
export async function paymentsRoutes(app: FastifyInstance) {
  app.post('/tenants/:tenantId/payments/offline',
    { preHandler: [authenticate, requireRole('cashier', 'accountant'), requireTenantMatch] },
    logOfflinePaymentHandler
  );
}
```

## Middleware Order (always this order)
1. `authenticate` — validates JWT, checks user_ver, checks blacklist
2. `requireTenantMatch` — validates X-Tenant-Id header matches JWT claim
3. `requireRole(...roles)` — RBAC check
4. `requireStepUp(action)` — for high-risk routes only
5. `requireIdempotencyKey` — for financial and workflow writes
6. Handler

## Standard Response Shape
```typescript
// Success
reply.send({ status: 'success', data: result, meta: { requestId, timestamp } });

// Error — use reply.loomisError() helper
reply.loomisError('FINANCE_PAYMENT_DUPLICATE', 'Payment already processed', 409);
```
Never return raw Fastify errors or unstructured objects.

## Error Code Namespace
Prefix error codes with the module name:
`IDENTITY_` `TENANT_` `HRM_` `ACADEMIC_` `STUDENT_` `FINANCE_` `LEDGER_` `RISK_` `REFERRAL_` `COMMS_` `WORKFLOW_` `COMPLIANCE_` `STORAGE_`

## Pagination
Use cursor-based pagination only. Never use offset/limit.
```typescript
// Query param: ?cursor=<base64-encoded-uuidv7>&limit=50
// Response includes: { data: [...], nextCursor: '<base64>' | null }
```

## Required Headers on Financial/Workflow Writes
```
Idempotency-Key: <uuid>      (required — reject 422 if absent)
X-Tenant-Id: <uuid>          (required on all tenant-scoped routes)
X-Request-Id: <uuid>         (generated by gateway if absent; always log this)
X-MFA-Token: <stepup-token>  (required on step-up routes)
```

## Validation
Use Zod schemas for ALL request body and query param validation. Register them as Fastify JSON schemas via `zodToJsonSchema`. Never access `req.body` without a validated type.

## File Uploads
NEVER accept file uploads directly on the API server. Always return a pre-signed S3 URL from `POST /api/v1/storage/upload-url` and let the client upload directly to S3.
